OL,3,CMajority of women 'not comfortable'
OL,4,Csharing political opinions online
OL,6,FThree quarters of women do not feel
OL,7,Fcomfortable expressing political
OL,8,Fopinions online over fears they will
OL,9,Fbe targeted with threats and
OL,10,Fharassment, according to new research
OL,11,Ffrom the Alan Turing Institute.
OL,13,FThe survey of 2,000 UK adults found
OL,14,Fthat the majority of women fear being
OL,15,Ftargeted by misogyny, trolling and
OL,16,Fother harmful online behaviour, and
OL,17,Fwomen were almost twice as likely than
OL,18,Fmen to say they had been negatively
OL,19,Faffected by an .
