OL,6,FThe Alan Turing Institute warned that
OL,7,Fwith much public discourse now
OL,8,Fhappening online, gender inequality in
OL,9,Fpublic voice could become more
OL,10,Fprevalent if women are too fearful to
OL,11,Fparticipate.
OL,13,FDr Florence Enock, senior research
OL,14,Fassociate at the Alan Turing Institute
OL,15,Fand co-lead on the research paper,
OL,16,Fsaid: "Taking steps to ensure that all
OL,17,Fmembers of society feel safe and able
OL,18,Fto participate in the online space is
OL,19,Fessential for an equal society.
